revisions.description: The initial version of this MIB file.

EnabledStatus.name: EnabledStatus
EnabledStatus.description: A simple status value for the object.

hpnicfMPortGroupLimitMinNumber.name: hpnicfMPortGroupLimitMinNumber
hpnicfMPortGroupLimitMinNumber.description: The lower limit of group-limit number.

hpnicfMPortGroupLimitMaxNumber.name: hpnicfMPortGroupLimitMaxNumber
hpnicfMPortGroupLimitMaxNumber.description: The upper limit of group-limit number.

hpnicfMPortGroupJoinTable.name: hpnicfMPortGroupJoinTable
hpnicfMPortGroupJoinTable.description: A table which is used for configuring a port in a specified VLAN to join a multicast group.

hpnicfMPortGroupJoinEntry.name: hpnicfMPortGroupJoinEntry
hpnicfMPortGroupJoinEntry.description: An entry which is used for configuring a port in a specified VLAN to join a multicast group.

hpnicfMPortGroupJoinVlanID.name: hpnicfMPortGroupJoinVlanID
hpnicfMPortGroupJoinVlanID.description: An index uniquely identifying a port in a specified VLAN which joined the multicast group.

hpnicfMPortGroupJoinAddressType.name: hpnicfMPortGroupJoinAddressType
hpnicfMPortGroupJoinAddressType.description: Type of the multicast IP address.

hpnicfMPortGroupJoinAddress.name: hpnicfMPortGroupJoinAddress
hpnicfMPortGroupJoinAddress.description: IP address of the group which the port belongs to, and it must be a valid multicast IP address.

hpnicfMPortGroupJoinStatus.name: hpnicfMPortGroupJoinStatus
hpnicfMPortGroupJoinStatus.description: This object is responsible for managing the creation and deletion of rows, which supports 'active', 'notReady', 'createAndGo', 'destroy'. Until instances of all corresponding columns are appropriately configured, the value of the corresponding instance of the hpnicfMPortGroupJoinStatus column is 'notReady'. In particular, a newly created row cannot be actived until the port belongs to the corresponding VLAN and IGMP or IGMP snooping is enabled on that VLAN.

hpnicfMPortGroupTable.name: hpnicfMPortGroupTable
hpnicfMPortGroupTable.description: A table containing information about the status of a port which joined a multicast group in the VLAN.

hpnicfMPortGroupEntry.name: hpnicfMPortGroupEntry
hpnicfMPortGroupEntry.description: An entry containing information about the status of a port which joined a multicast group in the VLAN.

hpnicfMPortGroupVlanID.name: hpnicfMPortGroupVlanID
hpnicfMPortGroupVlanID.description: An index uniquely identifies that a port belongs to a specified VLAN.

hpnicfMPortGroupAddress.name: hpnicfMPortGroupAddress
hpnicfMPortGroupAddress.description: IP address of the group which the port joined, and it must be a valid multicast IP address.

hpnicfMPortConfigTable.name: hpnicfMPortConfigTable
hpnicfMPortConfigTable.description: A table configuring the fast leave status, group limit number and group policy parameter on a port in the specified VLAN.

hpnicfMPortConfigEntry.name: hpnicfMPortConfigEntry
hpnicfMPortConfigEntry.description: An entry containing information about the fast leave status, group limit number and group policy parameter of a port in the specified VLAN.

hpnicfMPortGroupLimitNumber.name: hpnicfMPortGroupLimitNumber
hpnicfMPortGroupLimitNumber.description: The group limit number of the port.

hpnicfMPortFastLeaveStatus.name: hpnicfMPortFastLeaveStatus
hpnicfMPortFastLeaveStatus.description: The fast leave status of the port.

hpnicfMPortGroupPolicyParameter.name: hpnicfMPortGroupPolicyParameter
hpnicfMPortGroupPolicyParameter.description: The ACL number which is used as the group policy parameter of the port.

hpnicfMPortConfigRowStatus.name: hpnicfMPortConfigRowStatus
hpnicfMPortConfigRowStatus.description: The object is responsible for managing the creation and deletion of rows, which supports 'active', 'notReady', 'createAndGo' and 'destroy'.

hpnicfMPortGroupLimitReplace.name: hpnicfMPortGroupLimitReplace
hpnicfMPortGroupLimitReplace.description: This object is related to the object hpnicfMPortGroupLimitNumber. If the current IGMP group number is less than the value of hpnicfMPortGroupLimitNumber, any new IGMP group is permitted. If the current IGMP group number equals to the value of hpnicfMPortGroupLimitNumber and the value of this object is enabled, the group with the minimum multicast address will be replaced by the new group. If the current IGMP group number equals to the value of hpnicfMPortGroupLimitNumber and the value of this object is disabled, none of new group will be permitted.

hpnicfHostStaticJoinTable.name: hpnicfHostStaticJoinTable
hpnicfHostStaticJoinTable.description: A table used to configure a host on a port in a specified VLAN statically to join a multicast group.

hpnicfHostStaticJoinEntry.name: hpnicfHostStaticJoinEntry
hpnicfHostStaticJoinEntry.description: An entry used to configure a host on a port in a specified VLAN statically to join a multicast group.

hpnicfHostStaticJoinVlanID.name: hpnicfHostStaticJoinVlanID
hpnicfHostStaticJoinVlanID.description: An index uniquely identify the specified VLAN in which a host on a port statically joined the multicast group.

hpnicfHostStaticJoinAddressType.name: hpnicfHostStaticJoinAddressType
hpnicfHostStaticJoinAddressType.description: Type of the multicast IP address.

hpnicfHostStaticJoinAddress.name: hpnicfHostStaticJoinAddress
hpnicfHostStaticJoinAddress.description: IP address of the group which the host belongs to, and it must be a valid multicast IP address.

hpnicfHostStaticJoinStatus.name: hpnicfHostStaticJoinStatus
hpnicfHostStaticJoinStatus.description: This object is responsible for managing rows, which supports 'active', 'createAndGo' and 'destroy'.
